&gt;     This &#39;......&#39; indicates some problem starting up, even before any
&gt;     proxies come into play. It can be because the port it&#39;s seeking to use
&gt;     is already taken, or there are problems with the Java version on the
&gt;     machine. So suggestions include:
&gt;
&gt;     (1) View any heritrix_out.log or heritrix_dmesg.log file that may be
&gt;     created; it may have additional info.
&gt;
&gt;     (2) Set the environment variable &#39;FOREGROUND&#39; to &#39;true&#39; before
&gt;     launching
&gt;     to see Heritrix output in the launch shell (rather than for it to just
&gt;     try reporting its startup before returning you to the shell prompt).
&gt;
&gt;     (3) Make sure you&#39;re using the recommended version of Java: the
&gt;     Sun/Oracle 1.6+ JDK.
&gt;
&gt;     (4) Make sure nothing else is running on the port configured to be the
&gt;     administrative interface (usually 8080).
&gt;
&gt;     Heritrix can crawl through an HTTP proxy -- it requires extra
&gt;     configuration of the FetchHTTP processor -- but the failure to that
&gt;     would show up as a different, later problem than this.
&gt;
&gt;     - Gordon @ IA
